### Akeeba Panopticon API — Sysconfig
###
### Super-user only. Sensitive keys (dbpass, secret, smtppass, …) are omitted from
### list responses and are unreadable/unwritable through the API.

@hostname = https://panopticon.local
@token    = REPLACE-ME-WITH-A-REAL-TOKEN

### List all non-sensitive sysconfig parameters
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sysconfig
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Get a single non-sensitive parameter
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sysconfig/timezone
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Get a sensitive parameter — returns 404 `sysconfig.unknown_param` (do NOT use in production)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sysconfig/dbpass
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Set a single parameter (super-user only)
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/sysconfig/debug
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "value": true }

### Attempt to write a sensitive parameter — returns 403 auth.forbidden
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/sysconfig/dbpass
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "value": "nope" }

### Attempt to set an invalid value — returns 422 sysconfig.invalid_value
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/sysconfig/session_timeout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "value": -1 }
